# Number & temporal handling

Canonical: `agent-docs/architecture/number-handling.md`

## Core rule

LLMs **never** read, write, transform, or emit raw financial numbers or authoritative
dates/times/durations.

## Value flow

```
live data source / clock / market calendar
  → typed fixed-point ValueRef (k/v store)
  → deterministic calculator (unit algebra, sanity gauntlet)
  → lever resolution / band positions
  → execution
```

## Implementation checklist

- [ ] Model output fields for values typed as **ValueRef handles**, not numbers
- [ ] Calculator is sole producer of derived values; adapters/ledger/clock sole producers of sources
- [ ] Leak linter rejects digit and datetime patterns in model output text
- [ ] All "now" reads via injectable **clock module**
- [ ] Session math via **market calendar service**
- [ ] Timestamps in prompts: read-only orientation block only — never schedule from model text
- [ ] Fund router percentages: calc ops over ledger ValueRefs, not model-emitted amounts

## Math module (UI)

Auto-created per company, non-deletable — k/v browser, lineage graph, calc audit log.

When touching LLM prompts/schemas: run leak-lint tests. When touching calc: property-based
tests on unit algebra and fixed-point ops.
